Setup Instructions
==================

Server-side setup
----------------------------
1. Install Python 2.7 (http://www.python.org/getit/)
2. Install pip (http://www.pip-installer.org/en/latest/installing.html)
3. Run the following command in the same folder that contains `requirements.txt` (if that file exists)

    pip install requirements.txt
    
4. Run the appropriate application (if need be):

    python server.py

Client-side setup
-----------------
1. Download required files:

    - jQuery (http://jquery.com/download/)
    - Highcharts (http://www.highcharts.com/download)
    - ExtJS 4.2.1 (https://www.sencha.com/products/extjs/download/)
    - ExtJS Highcharts Extension (https://market.sencha.com/extensions/highcharts)

2. Copy required files to appropriate locations:

    - `jquery.dev.js` to `my_project/resources`
    - `highcharts.src.js` to `my_project/resources`
    - `highcharts-mote.src.js` to `my_project/resources`
    - ExtJS to `my_project/extjs`
    - ExtJS Highcharts Extension to `my_project/resources/Chart`

Running the examples
--------------------
1. After running `server.py`, visit `http://localhost:8000/index.html`
